#
# This program calculates the arithmetic mean of frequency-distributed data.
#
# Set PS 2.
# Use GOTO 0 0.
# Note: the printed table shows '-' at step 14; this file uses '=' as a documented
# booklet misprint correction. The printed example is consistent only if x1 is read
# as 2.5 instead of 3.
# If x1 is entered as 3 with the corrected '=', the program yields x_bar = 4.00,
# matching the direct weighted-mean calculation from the printed formula.
# Example:
#   GOTO 0 0
#   R/S
#   0.5 R/S  - h
#   2.5 R/S  - x1
#   3 R/S  - f1
#   6 R/S  - f2
#   8 R/S  - f3
#   5 R/S  - f4
#   2 R/S  - f5
#   1 R/S  - f6
#   SKP  - beende Eingabe und berechne Ergebnis(se)
#   R/S
#   -> 3.50
#   Alternative documented case:
#   mit x1 = 3 statt 2.5 liefert das korrigierte Programm 4.00.
#
00 090 R/S
01 055 STO
02 100 0
03 090 R/S
04 055 STO
05 103 3
06 090 R/S
07 055 STO
08 104 4
09 050 M+
10 101 1
11 012 *
12 056 RCL
13 103 3
14 080 =
15 050 M+
16 102 2
17 056 RCL
18 100 0
19 050 M+
20 103 3
21 056 RCL
22 103 3
23 093 GOTO
24 100 0
25 106 6
26 090 R/S
27 056 RCL
28 102 2
29 013 /
30 056 RCL
31 101 1
32 080 =
33 093 GOTO
34 100 0
35 100 0
36 099
37 099
38 099
39 099
40 099
41 099
42 099
43 099
44 099
45 099
46 099
47 099
48 099
49 099
50 099
51 099
52 099
53 099
54 099
55 099
56 099
57 099
58 099
59 099
60 099
61 099
62 099
63 099
64 099
65 099
66 099
67 099
68 099
69 099
70 099
71 099
